---
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro'

const homeHref = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.endsWith('/')
  ? import.meta.env.BASE_URL
  : `${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/`
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Petera is a local-first reminder app. This policy explains how Petera handles data."
  path="/privacy/"
>
  <section class="section-block">
    <div class="container prose-shell">
      <p class="eyebrow">Privacy</p>
      <h1 class="page-title">Petera Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="page-intro">
        Petera is a local-first reminder app. Petera does not require an account,
        does not sync reminder data to a server, and does not include advertising,
        analytics, or crash-reporting SDKs in the current release.
      </p>

      <div class="prose-card">
        <h2>Policy details</h2>
        <ul class="plain-list">
          <li>Effective date: 10 May 2026</li>
          <li>App: Petera</li>
          <li>
            Privacy contact: <a class="text-link-inline" href="mailto:support@petera.app"
              >support@petera.app</a
            >
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="prose-card">
        <h2>Data stored on your device</h2>
        <p>Petera stores app data locally on your device, including:</p>
        <ul class="plain-list">
          <li>reminders you create</li>
          <li>reminder scheduling state</li>
          <li>local notification scheduling metadata</li>
          <li>
            app settings such as language, theme, quiet hours, preferred days, History,
            and Insights settings
          </li>
          <li>optional local History entries</li>
          <li>optional local Insights activity</li>
          <li>a bounded local diagnostic event log used for troubleshooting</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          This data is used to provide Petera's reminder, notification, History,
          Insights, data export/import, and troubleshooting features.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose-card">
        <h2>Data sent to the developer</h2>
        <p>
          Petera does not automatically send reminder data, usage data, analytics,
          crash reports, or diagnostics to the developer.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose-card">
        <h2>User-initiated export, import, and sharing</h2>
        <p>
          Petera lets you manually export your local reminder data to a local JSON file.
          Anyone with access to that exported file may be able to read its contents.
        </p>
        <p>
          Petera also lets you manually import a Petera export file. Import replaces
          local reminders and saved data settings on the device. History and Insights
          data are cleared during import because they are not included in the export
          file.
        </p>
        <p>
          Petera can generate a diagnostic report when you open the support flow. The
          diagnostic report may include reminder identifiers, scheduled notification
          metadata, app settings, scheduler diagnostics, and recent structured app
          events. Reminder names are excluded unless you choose to include them.
          Diagnostic reports are saved or shared only when you choose to do so.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you share an export file or diagnostic report using another app or service,
          that app or service handles the shared file under its own privacy practices.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose-card">
        <h2>Notifications</h2>
        <p>
          Petera uses local notifications to surface reminders on your device.
          Notification permission is controlled by your operating system. On Android,
          Petera may ask for alarms and reminders access so scheduled local reminders
          can be delivered reliably.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose-card">
        <h2>Data retention and deletion</h2>
        <p>
          Reminder data remains on your device until you edit or delete it, import a
          replacement data file, clear app data, or uninstall Petera.
        </p>
        <p>
          History and Insights data are retained locally for up to 30 days in the current
          release. You can clear local History and Insights data from Settings.
        </p>
        <p>
          Because Petera does not automatically collect or store your data on developer
          servers in the current release, the developer does not hold a copy of your
          local app data to delete.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose-card">
        <h2>Children</h2>
        <p>Petera is not directed to children.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose-card">
        <h2>Changes</h2>
        <p>
          This policy may be updated when Petera's features or data practices change.
          The effective date above will be updated when the published policy changes.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose-actions">
        <a class="button button-primary" href={homeHref}>Back to home</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
